cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically with 3D pose estimation from 2D images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of geometric algorithms and optimization techniques for 3D pose estimation suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper deals with estimating the focal length, which is a parameter related to camera calibration, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
